{
  "text": "where n is a constant and represents a percentage of identity that is added to the curve to increase the stringency of the filter. For n = 0, the curve has an asymptote at identity of 20% around 100 amino acids in alignment length, but this value can be increased to 40% by using n = 20, which corresponds to a threshold for functional conservation [CITATION_1] .",
